The 35-year-old man appeared in the Bredasdorp Magistrates Court on Thursday. CAPE TOWN - The case against a man charged with the murder of a six-year-old Elim girl has been postponed until 18 April for a formal bail application. The 35-year-old man appeared in the Bredasdorp Magistrates Court on Thursday. Delvina Europa's body was found among bushes behind a school in the Elim community during a search by police and community members on Tuesday morning. Police are also investigating whether the minor was raped.